### Conflicts
Reviewers, this pull request conflicts with the following ones:

* [#17034](https://drahtbot.github.io/bitcoin_core_issue_redirect/r/17034.html) (Bip174 extensions by achow101)
* [#16463](
Concept ACK, could include more invalid tests?
Rebased to the latest master and added some more test cases to the rpc_psbt.json as @promag suggested.\n\nEdit: Additionally reverted a change that @achow101 asked.
Sorry, added the changes as a separate commit instead of amending, for easier review.

ACK b505d774eda28cbe965cd9d9ded3c9a83b9392fa, but needs squashing\n\nChecked the individual test cases by hand and verified they contain duplicate keys with values that meet the previous empty conditions. Also checked that those tests fail on master.
code review ACK https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16821/commits/9743432034586385cfef87df4b377c255ed0cba8\n\ndid not verify the test cases
I don't think this check for an unknown key is necessary in the same way the it is not needed for partial sigs or hd keypaths. It is a map of unknowns and we aren't checking if something is null.

You are correct, I left it for visual consistency (probably should have done the same for `PSBT_IN_PARTIAL_SIG`).

If you feel strong about it, will revert it for the unknowns.
Finally have reverted it for the unknowns.
